{
  "text": "There is compelling evidence that the medial temporal lobe plays a critical role in detecting novelty [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In particular, parts of the medial temporal lobe centred on the perirhinal cortex are strongly implicated in familiarity discrimination for individual stimulus items; typically, hippocampal novelty signals involve spatial or complex associational components [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Perirhinal cortex is a close neighbour of the hippocampal formation in the medial temporal lobe. It receives information from all over the cerebral cortex and has strong interconnections with the hippocampus.",
